sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Client as MCP Client<br/>(Claude, Cursor, etc.)
    participant Proxy as MCP Auth Adapter
    participant SSO as Upstream IdP
    participant MCPServer as MCP Server

    Note over Client, MCPServer: 1. Initialization
    Client->>MCPServer: Connects to server
    MCPServer-->>Client: Announces MCP Auth Adapter as Authorization Server
    Client->>Proxy: GET /.well-known/openid-configuration
    Proxy->>SSO: GET /.well-known/openid-configuration
    SSO-->>Proxy: Returns descriptor
    Proxy-->>Client: Returns filtered descriptor (adapted scopes, injected own endpoints)
    Note over Client, SSO: 2. Open Dynamic Client Registration (DCR)
    Client->>Proxy: POST /register
    Proxy-->>Client: Returns pre-configured fixed  client_id from Upstream IdP
    
    Note over Client, SSO: 3. Authorization & Token Issuance
    Client->>Proxy: GET /authorize (with client_id and  requested scopes)
    Note over Proxy: Intercepts & filters scopes (e.g. strips "offline_access")
    Proxy-->>Client: Redirects client to Upstream IdP  /authorize
    Client->>SSO: Authenticates user, consent screen shown
    SSO-->>Client: Issues Access Token via token exchange
    
    Note over Client, MCPServer: 4. Secure Resource Access & Access Token Validation
    Client->>MCPServer: Sends MCP request (e.g. tool call) with Access Token
    
    MCPServer->>Proxy: GET /.well-known/openid-configuration
    Proxy-->>MCPServer: Returns descriptor containing JWKS (Certificate) URI from Upstream IdP (loaded in step 5)
    MCPServer-->>SSO: Fetches Certificate used to sign Access Token
    MCPServer->>MCPServer: Validates the Acces Token signature & claims<br/>Authenticates and authorizes request
